Karan
Both "make it and eat" and "make it and have" are grammatically correct, but the choice depends on the context and personal preference.

"Make it and eat" is a straightforward and commonly used phrase, especially when referring to food. It simply means to prepare the dish and then consume it.

"Make it and have" is also correct and can be used interchangeably with "make it and eat." In some contexts, "have" might sound slightly more formal or polite, but both convey the same meaning.

Ultimately, you can use either phrase depending on what feels more natural to you or the tone you want to convey. Both convey the idea of preparing and enjoying the white sauce pasta.

In a separate bowl, combine 250g of mascarpone cheese with 50g of sugar until well combine 3. Combine both the mascarpone and whipped cream together and that’s the cream mixture 4. Dip the ladyfingers into strawberry milk ( if you don’t have strawberry milk, you can dip into strawberry juice or any sort of strawberry flavored mixture ) would recommend strawberry milk 5. Layer the ladyfingers, the cream accordingly with the video . 6. Cut the strawberries into thin slices and layer on top of the tiramisu and top it off with some icing sugar 🍓 ( i would definitely recommend adding more strawberries 🤣) 7. Veg Lollipop🌽🥕🫑 👉Ingredients: Potatoes - 4 (medium sized & Boiled) Capsicum - 1/2 (chopped) Carrot - 1 (grated) Sweet corn - 1/2 cup (boiled) Onion - 1 (chopped) Green chillies - 2 (chopped) Coriander leaves - 1/4 cup (chopped) Bread crumbs - 1 cup ( or more if needed) Salt as per taste Dry mango powder - 1/2 tsp Coriander powder - 1 tsp Garam masala - 1 tsp Red chilli powder - 1 tsp Black pepper powder - 1/2 tsp Ginger garlic paste - 1/2 tsp Kasuri methi - 1 tsp Chat masala - 1/2 tsp Mash the boiled potatoes and add the above ingredients and form a dough. Roll into round shaped balls. 👉For corn flour Slurry: Maida - 2 tbsp Corn flour slurry - 2 tbsp Water - 1/2 cup Salt - 1/2 tsp Mix into thick slurry Dip rolled balls in slurry and drain off Coat in panko bread crumbs You can also freeze at this stage and use later. Deep fry until golden brown and enjoy! #veglollipop #snack #indiancuisinecorner #indianfood #indiancuisinetelugu #foodblogger #foodtalksindia #reels #reelsinstagram #reelitfeelit #reelsvideo #foodporn #indianfood #indianrecipes #yummy #streetfood #instagood #instagram #instadaily #foodstagram #indiancuisine #indianstreetfood #telugublogger #telugufoodblog #instafam #foodie #foodblog
